Got to admit that was a good one, Ho Ho Ho,<br><br>
Thanks for the book bro, made the mailmen empty out his mail truck on the roadway yesterday. You said you send it and I knew you wouldn't lie.  <br><br>
Found it stashed away in the back of his jeep, with the Playboy magazines. Guess he wanted to read it himself. Made everyone else's mail late, but I got my book.<br><br>
Boy, you are a bad mean looking dude on the back cover of your book.<br><br>
Flag waving in the background, Assault helicopters flying in formation overhead. <br>
Little black beanie cap, Sunray sunglasses, macho man thick mustache, chubby face, Popeye shaped forearms, Giant hands numbered wrist watch, six fire watch ribbons, toilet seat cover medals, nineteen decorative patches and a can of pound cake and a pear tree.<br><br>
Did see that P-38 front and center of the front cover, now I knows you are a true brother. Small P-38 like the enlisted men carried, none of those BIG P-38S officers wore. Took me 24 hours just to go through the picture on the front and back cover, its got to be good. <br><br>
I did see you carried one of those sissy camouflaged poncho liners, no Marine in Nam would be caught sleeping in one of those silky feeling cover sheets. That stuff was for Airborne, Air Force and Navy personnel.<br><br>
Thanks Bro<br><br>
God Bless You &amp; God Bless America<br><br>
&quot;Welcome Home Bro!&quot;<br><br>
Cookie  <br>

